1.go to github
2.click on the desired  repository
3.inside it, click on the file/folder of your choice
4.locate the code icon and click on it
5.a url of the file/folder will be shown inside the code icon, copy it
6.after that. Head over to your file explorer
7.under your codes folder create a new one inside it 
  NOTE;If you do not afoler for your codes, create the folder inside your desktop 

8.inside that new folder, right click(a menu will appeaar)
9.click on the'open in terminal' option 
10.after the terminal appears type 'git clone (url of the file/folder you copied)' then enter
11.once the file has been cloned type  'cd (name of the folder you cloned)' then enter
12.after that  type'code .' then enter(the file/folder that was cloned will open in your vs. code)